Kingkong is a CLI showcase for rich help output.

Usage:
  kingkong <command> [flags]

Version:
  v0.0.0-test ({{GOOS}}/{{GOARCH}})

  -h, --help
          Show context-sensitive help.

Core Flags
  Common settings for every command.

      --config ($KINGKONG_CONFIG)
          Path to config file.
          [default: ./kingkong.yaml]
      --profile
          Runtime profile.
          [default: dev, choice: dev,staging,prod]
      --output
          Output format.
          [default: json, choice: json,yaml,text]
  -v, --verbose
          Enable verbose logging.
      --[no-]debug ($KINGKONG_DEBUG)
          Enable debug logging.

Network Flags
  Connection-related options.

      --host
          Bind address.
          [default: 127.0.0.1]
      --port
          Bind port.
          [default: 8080]

Lifecycle Commands
  Project setup and runtime operations.

  init [flags]
    Initialize a project.


  serve (run,server) <config> [<profile>] [flags]
    Run the service.


Examples:
  # Initialize a new project.
  kingkong init --template=go
  kingkong init --template=rust --force

  # Run with a custom config.
  kingkong serve ./configs/dev.yaml
  kingkong serve ./configs/prod.yaml prod

Environment:
  Use KINGKONG_CONFIG to override the config path.

Run "kingkong <command> --help" for more information on a command.
